00:36:49,897 --> 00:36:53,233
So let's advise our client to...
to accept the offer.

797
00:37:05,880 --> 00:37:07,580
(gunshot)

798
00:37:07,581 --> 00:37:09,716
(buzzer sounds)

799
00:37:16,757 --> 00:37:18,291
(gunshot)

800
00:37:19,126 --> 00:37:22,829
(buzzer sounds)

801
00:37:44,652 --> 00:37:47,120
So I seem to be a suspect.

802
00:37:47,121 --> 00:37:51,057
Apparently, internal affairs
is looking into my connection

803
00:37:51,058 --> 00:37:52,358
with the Arkin shooting.

804
00:37:52,359 --> 00:37:53,993
Yeah, I heard.

805
00:37:53,994 --> 00:37:56,930
This stuff seems to be
coming from your lawsuit.

806
00:37:56,931 --> 00:37:58,164
That's right.

807
00:37:58,165 --> 00:38:02,068
So why all the questions

808
00:38:02,069 --> 00:38:05,471
about what I do for friends?

809
00:38:05,472 --> 00:38:07,974
What, you thought I did it?

810
00:38:10,077 --> 00:38:11,644
Yeah.

811
00:38:13,547 --> 00:38:15,682
Go to hell.

812
00:38:20,654 --> 00:38:21,921
What?

813
00:38:21,922 --> 00:38:23,156
What?!

814
00:38:23,157 --> 00:38:24,991
Nothing. I just, um...

815
00:38:30,464 --> 00:38:32,098
I'm sorry.

816
00:38:39,607 --> 00:38:40,974
What is this?

817
00:38:40,975 --> 00:38:43,109
Who really tipped off Gorman.

818
00:38:53,420 --> 00:38:55,688
(Mic feedback)
One, two. Mic check, testing...

819
00:38:55,689 --> 00:38:57,991
So, is this just an
exoneration victory lap

820
00:38:57,992 --> 00:38:59,459
or is he going to announce?

821
00:38:59,460 --> 00:39:01,094
Gail, you'll find out
in one hour.

822
00:39:01,095 --> 00:39:02,562
Oh, come on.

823
00:39:02,563 --> 00:39:04,497
Mrs. Florrick going to
be on stage with him?

824
00:39:04,498 --> 00:39:05,565
(phone ringing)

825
00:39:05,566 --> 00:39:06,766
Excuse me.

826
00:39:06,767 --> 00:39:07,834
This is Gold.

827
00:39:07,835 --> 00:39:11,070
(distant Mic feedback squeals)

828
00:39:11,071 --> 00:39:12,872
I don't know.

829
00:39:12,873 --> 00:39:15,475
They're not going to leave us
alone- the press.

830
00:39:15,476 --> 00:39:17,410
(sighs) You're right.

831
00:39:20,614 --> 00:39:27,453
You know, I was reading
about these murals in Sienna.

832
00:39:27,454 --> 00:39:30,490
And one of them
showed good government.

833
00:39:30,491 --> 00:39:33,626
People happy.

834
00:39:33,627 --> 00:39:35,895
Buildings going up.

835
00:39:35,896 --> 00:39:38,064
Courts making good decisions.

836
00:39:38,065 --> 00:39:43,202
And on the opposite wall
was bad government.

837
00:39:43,203 --> 00:39:45,505
It was the same people,
but they were...

838
00:39:45,506 --> 00:39:46,739
They were unhappy,

839
00:39:46,740 --> 00:39:48,408
the courts were making
bad decisions.

840
00:39:48,409 --> 00:39:54,047
It occurred to me
that it only works

841
00:39:54,048 --> 00:39:56,816
if people step up...

842
00:39:56,817 --> 00:40:00,153
If you make the sacrifice.

843
00:40:00,154 --> 00:40:01,254
Look, I was just

844
00:40:01,255 --> 00:40:05,958
an okay state's attorney,
nothing special.

845
00:40:05,959 --> 00:40:09,262
But I want to be a great one.

846
00:40:09,263 --> 00:40:13,132
And I can't do it without you.

847
00:40:15,602 --> 00:40:17,336
I don't want the kids involved.

848
00:40:17,337 --> 00:40:18,504
They won't be.

849
00:40:18,505 --> 00:40:20,506
And I want to work.

850
00:40:20,507 --> 00:40:24,477
I want you to work.

851
00:40:37,925 --> 00:40:39,959
(clearing throat)

852
00:41:00,314 --> 00:41:02,582
A little more than a year ago,

853
00:41:02,583 --> 00:41:04,217
I stood at this podium

854
00:41:04,218 --> 00:41:07,220
and apologized to the public
and to my family

855
00:41:07,221 --> 00:41:11,257
about a personal failure.
(phone ringing)

856
00:41:11,258 --> 00:41:13,559
I made a very bad mistake.

857
00:41:13,560 --> 00:41:16,162
I betrayed my marital vows.

858
00:41:16,163 --> 00:41:17,330
Hello. Will?

859
00:41:17,331 --> 00:41:19,232
Alicia, hi.

860
00:41:19,233 --> 00:41:20,266
Where are you?

861
00:41:20,267 --> 00:41:21,334
Peter's press conference.

862
00:41:21,335 --> 00:41:23,269
Is everything all right?

863
00:41:23,270 --> 00:41:25,171
Yes.

864
00:41:25,172 --> 00:41:27,907
I was just thinking-
I don't want to go through life

865
00:41:27,908 --> 00:41:29,542
and think something
didn't happen

866
00:41:29,543 --> 00:41:31,210
just because
I didn't make myself clear.

867
00:41:31,211 --> 00:41:32,545
I can't hear you.

868
00:41:33,947 --> 00:41:37,016
I said I want
to make something clear.

869
00:41:37,017 --> 00:41:38,551
Hold on.

870
00:41:38,552 --> 00:41:40,019
PETER:
All those charges were dropped.

871
00:41:40,020 --> 00:41:42,555
That puts me back
where I belong.

872
00:41:43,857 --> 00:41:45,625
Okay, I just need to say it.

873
00:41:45,626 --> 00:41:47,727
We've been up and down,
back and forth,

874
00:41:47,728 --> 00:41:50,062
and I look at you, Alicia,

875
00:41:50,063 --> 00:41:51,297
and I think that...
Will...

876
00:41:51,298 --> 00:41:53,766
No, I just need to say this.
No.

877
00:41:53,767 --> 00:41:55,735
Show me the plan.

878
00:41:55,736 --> 00:41:57,203
The what?

879
00:41:57,204 --> 00:41:58,771
The plan.

880
00:41:58,772 --> 00:42:00,306
I get the romance.

881
00:42:00,307 --> 00:42:01,374
I need a plan.

882
00:42:01,375 --> 00:42:04,010
Not everything needs a plan.

883
00:42:04,011 --> 00:42:05,845
Everything that matters does.

884
00:42:05,846 --> 00:42:08,247
I have two kids that mean
the world to me.

885
00:42:08,248 --> 00:42:09,849
I have the press.

886
00:42:09,850 --> 00:42:10,817
They're just waiting

887
00:42:10,818 --> 00:42:11,951
for a whiff of a new scandal.

888
00:42:11,952 --> 00:42:13,386
And I have a husband.

889
00:42:13,387 --> 00:42:17,023
Justice is what this job
should be about.

890
00:42:17,024 --> 00:42:19,625
So if you want to cut
through all that noise,

891
00:42:19,626 --> 00:42:21,294
then show me a plan.

892
00:42:23,630 --> 00:42:25,731
Poetry is easy.

893
00:42:25,732 --> 00:42:27,333
It's the parent-teacher
conferences that are hard.

894
00:42:27,334 --> 00:42:28,367
Alicia, come on.

895
00:42:28,368 --> 00:42:30,136
I have to go now.
Come on.

896
00:42:30,137 --> 00:42:33,439
I... Okay.

897
00:42:36,009 --> 00:42:40,413
<i>PETER: Now I realize that
I cannot do this alone.</i>

898
00:42:40,414 --> 00:42:43,850
With your support, I hope to
become the state's attorney

899
00:42:43,851 --> 00:42:45,384
of Cook County once again.

900
00:42:45,385 --> 00:42:47,420
It won't be easy,
but it's necessary.

901
00:42:47,421 --> 00:42:49,088
You're going to make
my life harder.

902
00:42:49,089 --> 00:42:51,390
PETER: Change it we
can, change it we must,

903
00:42:51,391 --> 00:42:55,761
because Chicago once again
needs a change.

904
00:42:55,762 --> 00:42:58,998
Because Chicago once again
needs a new beginning.

905
00:42:58,999 --> 00:43:00,933
I believe I am that change,

906
00:43:00,934 --> 00:43:03,803
and I believe
that I am that new beginning.

907
00:43:03,804 --> 00:43:04,704
Thank you for listening.

908
00:43:04,705 --> 00:43:06,973
(cheering and applause)

909
00:43:12,179 --> 00:43:14,413
(reporters clamoring)

910
00:43:14,414 --> 00:43:15,581
Alicia.



